results.name: Minimal number of steps to reach 5*n from 5 using "Choix de Bruxelles" version 2 (cf. A323460).
comment: This is equally the minimal number of steps to reach 5*n from 5 using "Choix de Bruxelles" version 1 (cf. A323286). - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jan 24 2019
The sequence is well defined as we can reach any multiple of 5 starting from 5.
link: Rémy Sigrist, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000

Eric Angelini, Lars Blomberg, Charlie Neder, Remy Sigrist, and N. J. A. Sloane, "Choix de Bruxelles": A New Operation on Positive Integers, arXiv:1902.01444, Feb 2019; Fib. Quart. 57:3 (2019), 195-200.
